OL,3,CNI, capital gains, corporation tax:
OL,4,CWhat could we expect from Reeves'
OL,5,CBudget?
OL,7,FEmployers currently pay 13.8% on
OL,8,Fearnings above #175 a week, or #9,100
OL,9,Fa year per person, under Class 1 NI
OL,10,Fcontributions. It's deducted and set
OL,11,Faside for HMRC before wages are paid
OL,12,Fout.
OL,14,FA one percentage point increase in the
OL,15,FClass 1 rate could raise #8.45 billion
OL,16,Fover the 2025 to 2026 tax year, and a
OL,17,Ftwo percentage point hike could raise
OL,18,F#16.9 billion, according to data
OL,19,Fcompiled by HMRC and EY.
OL,21,FPension taxation
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/17
